<br>
For example, for Aailin, posting on the public board of Resolution was private domain, but for Ayrielle it was public domain.  He considered it okay to post there, she did not.  From there a host of other problems arise, leading to the current posting mess...<br>
<br>
Then, another look at how to resolve problems.  Ayrielle found that she could not fix the problems she saw. So, wanting to help (and intent should be counted in this), she posted a good bye post that also listed flaws... in order to try to help the guild.  She seemed earnest in her desires.  But on the other hand, Aailin sees only that she should've stayed and fixed it, or said nothing at all.  Aailin, if you should read this... try to keep in mind her intent was to help.  Yes, it may be condescending and brutal, but ... at least consider the problems (And I have no idea what they are) and see whether any of them are something that can be fixed. Ignore the source of the message, but instead just view the message by itself. If the message had been valid if Ayrielle had stayed, then it should still be valid with her leaving.<br>
<br>
The two together are a prime example of miscommunication. *sighs* As a bystander, I know them both only slightly, but reputation preceeds them both, and a good one at that. I hate to see folks arguing like this... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=erinitarcloudwalker>Erinitar Cloudwalker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/20/03 5:41 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: my 2 cents</span><hr size=1> I'm just wondering how long it takes Ayrielle to write one of these posts <br>
