<br>
I have run an area on an online game for 3-4 years now. Maybe more. I've lost count. Whenever anyone leaves my 'area' or group as it were, I actively seek out their feedback. Some of them post it publically, though I do not like it, I read it and try to consider it and apply it to where it goes and see if its just an angry person talking, or if there's some substance. Most of the time, folks, despite how we may detest the thought of it -- those issues have substance. Too many folks think that they do things right or that they're perfect though and refuse to see this -- I'm not saying that's the case here of course. I'm just pointing out that rather than yelling back and forth about who is right and who is wrong -- just let it disapate and meanwhile consider what HAS been said -- to both sides, even if you do not completely 100 % agree with what has been said. There may be some facts there and you maybe should examine more deeply the reason behind those comments.<br>
<br>
Thats just my opinion.<br>
