<br>
But you know something? In the end it all has to do with something called &quot;Loot or the Game.&quot; Because I did well with what I gained, and I think I deserved it all, but there were some times were I guess I could have went the extra mile and just killed a few goods here and there. Not going to happen, never will happen. What she did was a unique thing here. See in this world you have this part of you that looks at whoever is next to you thats &quot;Master&quot; or &quot;Sage&quot; or whatever, and you want to have more. You think about the 12.95, you think how cool it is to kill big Ol' Junk, and before you know it, you think you are in Fires of Heaven or something. <br>
<br>
If you are down with the loot and you are in a Roleplay guild, go /guildremove. If you are in the raiding guild and you want to roleplay it, then you need to do the same, its just that simple. Where are all of these high level roleplayers? I mean let me know, because for a roleplaying server, there is no mixture of a true roleplay guild with members above 60. I mean its going to come down to a raid, and its going to come down to the old arguements. I don't think there is even a place to even mention a storyline for one...hell knows I tried. <br>
<br>
Here is some food for thought to anyone that would consider themselves a roleplayer in this world. IF you want to stay away from contradictions, don't make yourself one. Get your guild, have your good times, and keep it real. Too many people faking it for the loot, be real. Don't act as if you are going to go that extra mile for a guild that you KNOW isn't going to go that extra mile for you. The one thing that I can say about Resolution, is that I know they went that route for me on countless occasions, but then I did the roleplay thing and they never gave me the boot for it. Damn it was hard however to keep doing it, but look what you sign up for. Unless my story is still out there for a possible origin...?<br>
<br>
Well, I talk too much. Good evening to you Resolution and well...times change, some folks stay the same. Ciao. <br>
